{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"I would like to talk today"},{"time":2000,"text":"about what I think is one of the greatest adventures"},{"time":4000,"text":"human beings have embarked upon,"},{"time":6000,"text":"which is the quest to understand the universe"},{"time":9000,"text":"and our place in it."},{"time":11000,"text":"My own interest in this subject, and my passion for it,"},{"time":14000,"text":"began rather accidentally."},{"time":16000,"text":"I had bought a copy of this book,"},{"time":19000,"text":"\"The Universe and Dr. Einstein\" --"},{"time":21000,"text":"a used paperback from a secondhand bookstore in Seattle."},{"time":24000,"text":"A few years after that, in Bangalore,"},{"time":27000,"text":"I was finding it hard to fall asleep one night,"},{"time":29000,"text":"and I picked up this book,"},{"time":31000,"text":"thinking it would put me to sleep in 10 minutes."},{"time":33000,"text":"And as it happened,"},{"time":35000,"text":"I read it from midnight to five in the morning in one shot."},{"time":38000,"text":"And I was left with this intense feeling"},{"time":41000,"text":"of awe and exhilaration"},{"time":43000,"text":"at the universe"},{"time":45000,"text":"and our own ability to understand as much as we do."},{"time":48000,"text":"And that feeling hasn't left me yet."}]},{"cues":[{"time":51000,"text":"That feeling was the trigger for me"},{"time":53000,"text":"to actually change my career --"},{"time":55000,"text":"from being a software engineer to become a science writer --"},{"time":58000,"text":"so that I could partake in the joy of science,"},{"time":61000,"text":"and also the joy of communicating it to others."},{"time":64000,"text":"And that feeling also led me"},{"time":66000,"text":"to a pilgrimage of sorts,"},{"time":68000,"text":"to go literally to the ends of the earth"},{"time":70000,"text":"to see telescopes, detectors,"},{"time":73000,"text":"instruments that people are building, or have built,"},{"time":76000,"text":"in order to probe the cosmos"},{"time":78000,"text":"in greater and greater detail."},{"time":80000,"text":"So it took me from places like Chile --"},{"time":82000,"text":"the Atacama Desert in Chile --"},{"time":84000,"text":"to Siberia,"},{"time":86000,"text":"to underground mines"},{"time":88000,"text":"in the Japanese Alps, in Northern America,"},{"time":90000,"text":"all the way to Antarctica"},{"time":92000,"text":"and even to the South Pole."}]},{"cues":[{"time":94000,"text":"And today I would like to share with you"},{"time":96000,"text":"some images, some stories of these trips."},{"time":99000,"text":"I have been basically spending the last few years"},{"time":101000,"text":"documenting the efforts"},{"time":103000,"text":"of some extremely intrepid men and women"},{"time":106000,"text":"who are putting,"},{"time":108000,"text":"literally at times, their lives at stake"},{"time":110000,"text":"working in some very remote and very hostile places"},{"time":113000,"text":"so that they may gather the faintest signals from the cosmos"},{"time":117000,"text":"in order for us to understand this universe."}]},{"cues":[{"time":120000,"text":"And I first begin with a pie chart --"},{"time":122000,"text":"and I promise this is the only pie chart"},{"time":124000,"text":"in the whole presentation --"},{"time":126000,"text":"but it sets up the state of our knowledge of the cosmos."},{"time":130000,"text":"All the theories in physics that we have today"},{"time":133000,"text":"properly explain what is called normal matter --"},{"time":135000,"text":"the stuff that we're all made of --"},{"time":137000,"text":"and that's four percent of the universe."},{"time":139000,"text":"Astronomers and cosmologists and physicists think"},{"time":142000,"text":"that there is something called dark matter in the universe,"},{"time":145000,"text":"which makes up 23 percent of the universe,"},{"time":147000,"text":"and something called dark energy,"},{"time":149000,"text":"which permeates the fabric of space-time,"},{"time":151000,"text":"that makes up another 73 percent."},{"time":153000,"text":"So if you look at this pie chart, 96 percent of the universe,"},{"time":156000,"text":"at this point in our exploration of it,"},{"time":158000,"text":"is unknown or not well understood."},{"time":161000,"text":"And most of the experiments, telescopes that I went to see"},{"time":164000,"text":"are in some way addressing this question,"},{"time":167000,"text":"these two twin mysteries of dark matter and dark energy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":170000,"text":"I will take you first to an underground mine"},{"time":172000,"text":"in Northern Minnesota"},{"time":174000,"text":"where people are looking"},{"time":176000,"text":"for something called dark matter."},{"time":178000,"text":"And the idea here is that they are looking for a sign"},{"time":181000,"text":"of a dark matter particle hitting one of their detectors."},{"time":184000,"text":"And the reason why they have to go underground"},{"time":186000,"text":"is that, if you did this experiment on the surface of the Earth,"},{"time":189000,"text":"the same experiment would be swamped by signals"},{"time":191000,"text":"that could be created by things like cosmic rays,"},{"time":193000,"text":"ambient radio activity,"},{"time":195000,"text":"even our own bodies. You might not believe it,"},{"time":198000,"text":"but even our own bodies are radioactive enough to disturb this experiment."},{"time":201000,"text":"So they go deep inside mines"},{"time":204000,"text":"to find a kind of environmental silence"},{"time":206000,"text":"that will allow them to hear"},{"time":208000,"text":"the ping of a dark matter particle hitting their detector."}]},{"cues":[{"time":211000,"text":"And I went to see one of these experiments,"},{"time":213000,"text":"and this is actually -- you can barely see it,"},{"time":215000,"text":"and the reason for that is it's entirely dark in there --"},{"time":218000,"text":"this is a cavern that was left behind by the miners"},{"time":221000,"text":"who left this mine in 1960."},{"time":223000,"text":"And physicists came and started using it"},{"time":225000,"text":"sometime in the 1980s."},{"time":227000,"text":"And the miners in the early part of the last century"},{"time":230000,"text":"worked, literally, in candlelight."},{"time":232000,"text":"And today, you would see this inside the mine,"},{"time":234000,"text":"half a mile underground."},{"time":236000,"text":"This is one of the largest underground labs in the world."},{"time":238000,"text":"And, among other things, they're looking for dark matter."}]},{"cues":[{"time":241000,"text":"There is another way to search for dark matter,"},{"time":243000,"text":"which is indirectly."},{"time":245000,"text":"If dark matter exists in our universe,"},{"time":247000,"text":"in our galaxy,"},{"time":249000,"text":"then these particles should be smashing together"},{"time":251000,"text":"and producing other particles that we know about --"},{"time":254000,"text":"one of them being neutrinos."},{"time":256000,"text":"And neutrinos you can detect"},{"time":258000,"text":"by the signature they leave"},{"time":260000,"text":"when they hit water molecules."},{"time":262000,"text":"When a neutrino hits a water molecule"},{"time":264000,"text":"it emits a kind of blue light,"},{"time":266000,"text":"a flash of blue light,"},{"time":268000,"text":"and by looking for this blue light,"},{"time":270000,"text":"you can essentially understand something about the neutrino"},{"time":272000,"text":"and then, indirectly, something about the dark matter"},{"time":275000,"text":"that might have created this neutrino."},{"time":277000,"text":"But you need very, very large volumes of water"},{"time":280000,"text":"in order to do this."},{"time":282000,"text":"You need something like tens of megatons of water --"},{"time":284000,"text":"almost a gigaton of water --"},{"time":286000,"text":"in order to have any chance of catching this neutrino."},{"time":289000,"text":"And where in the world would you find such water?"},{"time":291000,"text":"Well the Russians have a tank in their own backyard."}]},{"cues":[{"time":294000,"text":"This is Lake Baikal."},{"time":296000,"text":"It is the largest lake in the world. It's 800 km long."},{"time":299000,"text":"It's about 40 to 50 km wide"},{"time":301000,"text":"in most places,"},{"time":303000,"text":"and one to two kilometers deep."},{"time":305000,"text":"And what the Russians are doing"},{"time":307000,"text":"is they're building these detectors"},{"time":309000,"text":"and immersing them about a kilometer beneath the surface of the lake"},{"time":312000,"text":"so that they can watch for these flashes of blue light."},{"time":315000,"text":"And this is the scene that greeted me when I landed there."},{"time":318000,"text":"This is Lake Baikal"},{"time":320000,"text":"in the peak of the Siberian winter."},{"time":322000,"text":"The lake is entirely frozen."},{"time":324000,"text":"And the line of black dots"},{"time":327000,"text":"that you see in the background,"},{"time":329000,"text":"that's the ice camp where the physicists are working."},{"time":331000,"text":"The reason why they have to work in winter"},{"time":333000,"text":"is because they don't have the money to work in summer and spring,"},{"time":336000,"text":"which, if they did that,"},{"time":338000,"text":"they would need ships and submersibles to do their work."},{"time":340000,"text":"So they wait until winter --"},{"time":342000,"text":"the lake is completely frozen over --"},{"time":344000,"text":"and they use this meter-thick ice"},{"time":346000,"text":"as a platform on which to establish their ice camp and do their work."}]},{"cues":[{"time":349000,"text":"So this is the Russians working on the ice"},{"time":353000,"text":"in the peak of the Siberian winter."},{"time":355000,"text":"They have to drill holes in the ice,"},{"time":357000,"text":"dive down into the water -- cold, cold water --"},{"time":359000,"text":"to get hold of the instrument, bring it up,"},{"time":362000,"text":"do any repairs and maintenance that they need to do,"},{"time":365000,"text":"put it back and get out before the ice melts."},{"time":367000,"text":"Because that phase of solid ice lasts for two months"},{"time":369000,"text":"and it's full of cracks."},{"time":371000,"text":"And you have to imagine, there's an entire sea-like lake"},{"time":374000,"text":"underneath, moving."},{"time":376000,"text":"I still don't understand this one Russian man"},{"time":379000,"text":"working in his bare chest,"},{"time":381000,"text":"but that tells you how hard he was working."},{"time":384000,"text":"And these people, a handful of people,"},{"time":386000,"text":"have been working for 20 years,"},{"time":388000,"text":"looking for particles that may or may not exist."},{"time":390000,"text":"And they have dedicated their lives to it."},{"time":393000,"text":"And just to give you an idea,"},{"time":395000,"text":"they have spent 20 million over 20 years."},{"time":398000,"text":"It's very harsh conditions."},{"time":400000,"text":"They work on a shoestring budget."},{"time":402000,"text":"The toilets there are literally holes in the ground"},{"time":404000,"text":"covered with a wooden shack."},{"time":407000,"text":"And it's that basic,"},{"time":409000,"text":"but they do this every year."}]},{"cues":[{"time":411000,"text":"From Siberia to the Atacama Desert in Chile,"},{"time":414000,"text":"to see something called The Very Large Telescope."},{"time":416000,"text":"The Very Large Telescope"},{"time":418000,"text":"is one of these things that astronomers do --"},{"time":420000,"text":"they name their telescopes rather unimaginatively."},{"time":422000,"text":"I can tell you for a fact,"},{"time":424000,"text":"that the next one that they're planning is called The Extremely Large Telescope."},{"time":427000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":429000,"text":"And you wouldn't believe it,"},{"time":431000,"text":"but the one after that is going to be called The Overwhelmingly Large Telescope."},{"time":434000,"text":"But nonetheless,"},{"time":436000,"text":"it's an extraordinary piece of engineering."},{"time":438000,"text":"These are four 8.2 meter telescopes."},{"time":441000,"text":"And these telescopes, among other things,"},{"time":443000,"text":"they're being used to study"},{"time":445000,"text":"how the expansion of the universe is changing with time."},{"time":448000,"text":"And the more you understand that,"},{"time":450000,"text":"the better you would understand"},{"time":452000,"text":"what this dark energy that the universe is made of is all about."}]},{"cues":[{"time":455000,"text":"And one piece of engineering that I want to leave you with"},{"time":458000,"text":"as regards this telescope"},{"time":460000,"text":"is the mirror."},{"time":462000,"text":"Each mirror, there are four of them,"},{"time":464000,"text":"is made of a single piece of glass,"},{"time":466000,"text":"a monolithic piece of high-tech ceramic,"},{"time":468000,"text":"that has been ground down and polished to such accuracy"},{"time":471000,"text":"that the only way to understand what that is"},{"time":474000,"text":"is [to] imagine a city like Paris,"},{"time":476000,"text":"with all its buildings and the Eiffel Tower,"},{"time":479000,"text":"if you grind down Paris to that kind of accuracy,"},{"time":482000,"text":"you would be left with bumps that are one millimeter high."},{"time":486000,"text":"And that's the kind of polishing that these mirrors have endured."},{"time":489000,"text":"An extraordinary set of telescopes."},{"time":491000,"text":"Here's another view of the same."},{"time":493000,"text":"The reason why you have to build these telescopes"},{"time":495000,"text":"in places like the Atacama Desert"},{"time":497000,"text":"is because of the high altitude desert."},{"time":500000,"text":"The dry air is really good for telescopes,"},{"time":503000,"text":"and also, the cloud cover is below the summit of these mountains"},{"time":505000,"text":"so that the telescopes have"},{"time":507000,"text":"about 300 days of clear skies."}]},{"cues":[{"time":509000,"text":"Finally, I want to take you to Antarctica."},{"time":511000,"text":"I want to spend most of my time on this part of the world."},{"time":515000,"text":"This is cosmology's final frontier."},{"time":517000,"text":"Some of the most amazing experiments,"},{"time":519000,"text":"some of the most extreme experiments,"},{"time":521000,"text":"are being done in Antarctica."},{"time":523000,"text":"I was there to view something called a long-duration balloon flight,"},{"time":526000,"text":"which basically takes telescopes and instruments"},{"time":529000,"text":"all the way to the upper atmosphere,"},{"time":531000,"text":"the upper stratosphere, 40 km up."},{"time":534000,"text":"And that's where they do their experiments,"},{"time":536000,"text":"and then the balloon, the payload, is brought down."},{"time":539000,"text":"So this is us landing on the Ross Ice Shelf in Antarctica."},{"time":542000,"text":"That's an American C-17 cargo plane"},{"time":544000,"text":"that flew us from New Zealand"},{"time":546000,"text":"to McMurdo in Antarctica."},{"time":548000,"text":"And here we are about to board our bus."},{"time":550000,"text":"And I don't know if you can read the lettering,"},{"time":552000,"text":"but it says, \"Ivan the Terribus.\""},{"time":555000,"text":"And that's taking us to McMurdo."}]},{"cues":[{"time":558000,"text":"And this is the scene that greets you in McMurdo."},{"time":561000,"text":"And you barely might be able to make out"},{"time":563000,"text":"this hut here."},{"time":565000,"text":"This hut was built by Robert Falcon Scott and his men"},{"time":568000,"text":"when they first came to Antarctica"},{"time":570000,"text":"on their first expedition to go to the South Pole."},{"time":572000,"text":"Because it's so cold,"},{"time":574000,"text":"the entire contents of that hut is still as they left it,"},{"time":577000,"text":"with the remnants of the last meal they cooked still there."},{"time":580000,"text":"It's an extraordinary place."},{"time":582000,"text":"This is McMurdo itself. About a thousand people work here in summer,"},{"time":585000,"text":"and about 200 in winter"},{"time":587000,"text":"when it's completely dark for six months."}]},{"cues":[{"time":589000,"text":"I was here to see the launch"},{"time":591000,"text":"of this particular type of instrument."},{"time":593000,"text":"This is a cosmic ray experiment"},{"time":595000,"text":"that has been launched all the way to the upper-stratosphere"},{"time":598000,"text":"to an altitude of 40 km."},{"time":600000,"text":"What I want you to imagine is this is two tons in weight."},{"time":603000,"text":"So you're using a balloon"},{"time":605000,"text":"to carry something that is two tons"},{"time":607000,"text":"all the way to an altitude of 40 km."},{"time":610000,"text":"And the engineers, the technicians, the physicists"},{"time":613000,"text":"have all got to assemble on the Ross Ice Shelf,"},{"time":616000,"text":"because Antarctica -- I won't go into the reasons why --"},{"time":619000,"text":"but it's one of the most favorable places for doing these balloon launches,"},{"time":621000,"text":"except for the weather."},{"time":623000,"text":"The weather, as you can imagine,"},{"time":625000,"text":"this is summer, and you're standing on 200 ft of ice."},{"time":627000,"text":"And there's a volcano behind,"},{"time":629000,"text":"which has glaciers at the very top."},{"time":631000,"text":"And what they have to do"},{"time":633000,"text":"is they have to assemble the entire balloon --"},{"time":635000,"text":"the fabric, parachute and everything -- on the ice"},{"time":638000,"text":"and then fill it up with helium."},{"time":640000,"text":"And that process takes about two hours."}]},{"cues":[{"time":642000,"text":"And the weather can change as they're putting together this whole assembly."},{"time":645000,"text":"For instance, here they are laying down the balloon fabric behind,"},{"time":648000,"text":"which is eventually going to be filled up with helium."},{"time":651000,"text":"Those two trucks you see at the very end"},{"time":653000,"text":"carry 12 tanks each of compressed helium."},{"time":656000,"text":"Now, in case the weather changes before the launch,"},{"time":659000,"text":"they have to actually pack everything back up into their boxes"},{"time":662000,"text":"and take it out back to McMurdo Station."},{"time":665000,"text":"And this particular balloon,"},{"time":667000,"text":"because it has to launch two tons of weight,"},{"time":669000,"text":"is an extremely huge balloon."},{"time":672000,"text":"The fabric alone weighs two tons."},{"time":674000,"text":"In order to minimize the weight,"},{"time":677000,"text":"it's very thin, it's as thin as a sandwich wrapper."},{"time":679000,"text":"And if they have to pack it back,"},{"time":681000,"text":"they have to put it into boxes"},{"time":683000,"text":"and stamp on it so that it fits into the box again --"},{"time":686000,"text":"except, when they did it first,"},{"time":688000,"text":"it would have been done in Texas."},{"time":690000,"text":"Here, they can't do it with the kind shoes they're wearing,"},{"time":693000,"text":"so they have to take their shoes off,"},{"time":695000,"text":"get barefoot into the boxes, in this cold,"},{"time":697000,"text":"and do that kind of work."},{"time":699000,"text":"That's the kind of dedication these people have."}]},{"cues":[{"time":701000,"text":"Here's the balloon being filled up with helium,"},{"time":703000,"text":"and you can see it's a gorgeous sight."},{"time":705000,"text":"Here's a scene"},{"time":707000,"text":"that shows you the balloon and the payload end-to-end."},{"time":709000,"text":"So the balloon is being filled up with helium on the left-hand side,"},{"time":712000,"text":"and the fabric actually runs all the way to the middle"},{"time":715000,"text":"where there's a piece of electronics and explosives"},{"time":718000,"text":"being connected to a parachute,"},{"time":720000,"text":"and then the parachute is then connected to the payload."},{"time":722000,"text":"And remember, all this wiring is being done"},{"time":724000,"text":"by people in extreme cold, in sub-zero temperatures."},{"time":727000,"text":"They're wearing about 15 kg of clothing and stuff,"},{"time":730000,"text":"but they have to take their gloves off in order to do that."},{"time":733000,"text":"And I would like to share with you a launch."}]},{"cues":[{"time":736000,"text":"(Video) Radio: Okay, release the balloon,"},{"time":738000,"text":"release the balloon, release the balloon."}]},{"cues":[{"time":769000,"text":"Anil Ananthaswamy: And I'll finally like to leave you with two images."},{"time":772000,"text":"This is an observatory in the Himalayas, in Ladakh in India."},{"time":775000,"text":"And the thing I want you to look at here"},{"time":777000,"text":"is the telescope on the right-hand side."},{"time":779000,"text":"And on the far left there"},{"time":781000,"text":"is a 400 year-old Buddhist monastery."},{"time":783000,"text":"This is a close-up of the Buddhist monastery."},{"time":785000,"text":"And I was struck by the juxtaposition"},{"time":788000,"text":"of these two enormous disciplines that humanity has."},{"time":791000,"text":"One is exploring the cosmos on the outside,"},{"time":794000,"text":"and the other one is exploring our interior being."},{"time":796000,"text":"And both require silence of some sort."}]},{"cues":[{"time":799000,"text":"And what struck me was"},{"time":801000,"text":"every place that I went to to see these telescopes,"},{"time":803000,"text":"the astronomers and cosmologists"},{"time":805000,"text":"are in search of a certain kind of silence,"},{"time":807000,"text":"whether it's silence from radio pollution"},{"time":809000,"text":"or light pollution or whatever."},{"time":812000,"text":"And it was very obvious"},{"time":814000,"text":"that, if we destroy these silent places on Earth,"},{"time":816000,"text":"we will be stuck on a planet without the ability to look outwards,"},{"time":819000,"text":"because we will not be able to understand the signals that come from outer space."}]},{"cues":[{"time":822000,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":824000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}